item.title: CVE-2020-9255|2024-08-04T10:19:20.093Z -- huawei -- honor%2010
item.description: Huawei Honor 10 smartphones with versions earlier than 10.0.0.178(C00E178R1P4) have a denial of service vulnerability. Certain service in the system does not sufficiently validate certain parameter which is received, the attacker should trick the user into installing a malicious application, successful exploit could cause a denial of service condition.
